org.locationtech.geowave.core.ingest.hdfs.mapreduce

Interface IngestWithMapper<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - data type for intermediate data
    O - data type that will be ingested into GeoWave
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataAdapterProvider<O>, IngestPluginBase<I,O>, Persistable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLocalIngestWithMapper.InternalIngestWithMapper, AbstractSimpleFeatureIngestPlugin.AbstractIngestSimpleFeatureWithMapper, GDELTIngestPlugin.IngestGDELTFromHdfs, GeoLifeIngestPlugin.IngestGeoLifeFromHdfs, GeoWaveAvroIngestPlugin.IngestAvroFeaturesFromHdfs, GpxIngestPlugin.IngestGpxTrackFromHdfs, Stanag4676IngestPlugin.IngestWithReducerImpl, TdriveIngestPlugin.IngestTdrivePointFromHdfs, TwitterIngestPlugin.IngestTwitterFromHdfs

    public interface IngestWithMapper<I,O>
extends IngestPluginBase<I,O>, Persistable
    This interface is used by the IngestFromHdfsPlugin to implement ingestion within a mapper only. The implementation will be directly persisted to a mapper and called to produce GeoWaveData to be written.
